article.headline: UC Davis 73, Pacific 64
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Harrison DuPont had 17 points and eight rebounds to lead five UC Davis players scoring in double figures in a 73-64 victory against Pacific on Tuesday night. Tyler Les scored 15 points, Paolo Mancasola 13 and Josh Ritchart and Eddie Miller 10 each for the Aggies (3-22, 2-11 Big West), who have won two of three contests after an 18-game losing streak. Lorenzo McCloud had 14 points and Travis Fulton and Khalil Kelley 12 apiece for the Tigers (10-15, 6-7). DuPont scored 11 points during an 19-5 run during a 6:22 stretch of the second half that gave UC Davis control. The surge put the Aggies up 60-47 with 5:50 remaining, and Pacific got no closer than seven points the rest of the way.
